    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-26T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="833"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7490F/10–2644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="98" xml:id="d833fn98">Repeated to the Minister in Saudi
                        Arabia as telegram 221, October 26, 2 p.m., with the request that he report
                        to the Department such detailed information as he might have regarding the
                        questions raised therein (811.7490F/10–2144).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-26T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 26, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8924. ReDepts 8183, October 6, 8 p.m. Legation at Jidda has reported that British
                    authorities in London object to establishment of Saudi Arabian Government radio
                    station on security grounds and state that American censors have concurred with
                    the British in this regard. Jidda has not reported, however, who or where these
                    American censors are or the circumstances under which the alleged concurrence
                    was given. Please report fully to the Department on this matter <pb facs="0776"
                        n="764" xml:id="pg_764"/> at the earliest possible moment, bearing in mind
                    the December 1 deadline for giving notice.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Jidda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
